      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOKYO ROSE NZ (3) powered back into form with a win at Listed level in Sydney last start, coming from a wider barrier than this to score by 3.3m. Classy mare who is well served by the lower draw so is a big chance to go back to back. STENO (4) continued her consistent form when she came from the widest barrier for third to Tokyo Rose last start. That added to a string of top-three finishes at Menangle that includes a Sibelia Stakes win and a second to flying mare Captains Mistress in the G1 Queen Elizabeth II Mile. Hasn't missed a place at this distance range and a lower draw could see her back in the winners' list. LUX AETERNA (9) draws on the back row but took her strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent with a win last month and has been close up in Sydney in both runs since. SALLY BIGTIME (8) tackles some good mares tonight but draws for a trail and is hard to knock after winning four of her last five here. A low draw can see TREMENDOUS SENSATION NZ (1) competitive again.",
